[[File:Monoblock board.jpg|thumb|'''Monokub''' ({{lang-ru|Монокуб}}) [[motherboard]] with one [[Elbrus-2C+]] [[CPU]] at 500 MHz]] {{Redirects|Monocube|the geometric object|cube}}
'''Monokub''' ({{lang-ru|Монокуб}}) is a computer [[motherboard]] based on the Russian [[Elbrus 2000]] computer architecture, which form the basis for the [[Monoblock PC]] office workstation.<ref name="Kraftway1" /> <ref name="Kraftway2" />
The [[motherboard]] has a [[miniITX]] formfactor and contains a single [[Elbrus-2C+]] [[microprocessor]] with a clock frequency of 500&nbsp;MHz. The [[memory controller]] provides a dual-channel memory mode. The board has two [[DDR2-800]] memory slots, which enables up to 16&nbsp;GB of [[Random-access memory|RAM]] memory (using [[ECC memory|ECC]] modules). It also supports expansion boards using [[PCI Express]] x16 bus. In addition there is an on-board Gigabit [[Ethernet]] interface, 4 USB 2.0, [[RS-232]] interface, [[Digital Visual Interface|DVI]] connector and audio input/output ports.<ref name="Monokub1" /><ref name="Monokub2" />
