{{Infobox company | name = Trazzler | logo = | caption = | type = | traded_as = | genre = <!-- Only used with media and publishing companies --> | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = 2006 | founder = Adam Rugel, Biz Stone | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location_city = | location_country = | locations = | area_served = | key_people = | industry = | products = | production = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = <!-- Only used with financial services companies --> | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|trazzler.com}} | footnotes = | intl = }}
'''Trazzler''' is a [[Tourist destination|travel destination]] [[Mobile app|app]] that specializes in unique and local destinations. The initial concept was developed by Adam Rugel and [[Biz Stone]] in 2006 at [[Twitter|Twitter's]] original offices under the name "71 miles".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tnooz.com/2012/08/29/how-to/marketing-a-destination-mobile-app-the-sweat-equity-approach/ |title=Marketing a destination mobile app – the sweat equity approach |author= |date=August 29, 2012 |work= |publisher=Talking Travel Tech |accessdate=September 17, 2012}}</ref> More than 10,000 writers and photographers have contributed and more than $350,000 in freelance contracts have been issued as a result of Trazzeler's weekly writing and photography contests.<ref name="OP">{{cite web |url=http://openplac.es/contests |title=Writers and Photographers: Contribute |author= |date= |work= |publisher=Openplac.es |accessdate=September 17, 2012}}</ref> Investors in the company include SV Angel, [[Steve Case|AOL Founder Steve Case]], and the Twitter founders, [[Evan Williams (Internet entrepreneur)|Evan Williams]], [[Jack Dorsey]], and Biz Stone.<ref name="TC">{{cite web |url=https://techcrunch.com/2010/06/07/trazzler-gets-1-million-from-star-investors-takes-a-page-from-twitters-playbook-video/ |title=Trazzler Gets $1 Million From Star Investors, Takes a Page From Twitter’s Playbook |author=Evenlyn Rusli |date=June 7, 2010 |work= |publisher=TechCrunch |accessdate=September 17, 2012}}</ref> The company's partners are the [[Chicago|City of Chicago]], Hawaii Tourism Authority, [[Fairmont Hotels and Resorts|Fairmont Hotels & Resorts]], [[Salon (website)|Salon.com]], and [[Air New Zealand]]. Trazzler is designed for use on the [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]], and [[Facebook]].<ref name="TNW">{{cite web |url=https://thenextweb.com/apps/2011/10/05/biz-stones-trazzler-gives-you-recommendations-on-local-places-to-visit-based-on-photos/ |title=Biz Stone’s Trazzler gives you recommendations on local places to visit based on photos |author=Drew Olanoff |date=October 5, 2011 |work= |publisher=TheNextWeb.com |accessdate=September 17, 2012}}</ref><ref name="AA">{{cite web |url=http://www.appolicious.com/tech/articles/9715-trazzlers-personality-driven-results-tell-you-what-sights-to-see |title=Trazzler’s personality-driven results tell you what sights to see |author=Kathryn Swartz |date=October 5, 2011 |work= |publisher=Appolicious Advisor |accessdate=September 17, 2012}}</ref>
